title: Collier's
description:
Collier's V1 1-4, V2 1-2

V1 - Fantagraphics, 1991-1998, 28 pages each
V2 - Drawn & Quarterly, 2001-2003, 28 pages each

Written and Illustrated by David Collier

Not to be confused with the magazine that ran from 1888-1957 and then again in 2012. They bare no relation to one another.

One of those mostly forgotten but generally really great books that was randomly published over the years by Fantagraphics, D&Q, or the like (or in this case, both of them). Seems to be partly auto-biographical, but is definitely along the lines of the alternative, off-center, creator-centric stuff I usually upload. Recommended
